  "prompt": "What language was spoken in the period of Lord Rama?",
  "response": "During the period of Lord Rama, which is traditionally associated with the Treta Yuga in Hindu mythology, the language spoken was Sanskrit. Specifically, it would have been Vedic Sanskrit, an earlier form of the language that predates Classical Sanskrit.\n\nSanskrit was the primary language of communication among the upper classes, scholars, and royalty in ancient India. The epic Ramayana, which narrates the story of Lord Rama, was originally composed in Sanskrit by the sage Valmiki.\n\nIt's important to note that while this is the traditional understanding, the exact historical timeline and linguistic details of Lord Rama's period are subjects of ongoing scholarly debate and research. Archaeological and linguistic evidence about the precise period is still being studied by historians and scholars.",
